From: Stephen Brodie <author@example.com>
Date: Thu, 1 May 2026
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] ALSA: usb-audio: Make media pad link failure non-fatal in snd_media_stream_init

On the Apogee ONEv2 (0c60:0017), media_create_pad_link() fails
during snd_media_stream_init(). The existing code uses
goto remove_intf_link on this failure, which tears down the
entire PCM open sequence and prevents the playback PCM from
opening at all.

Changing goto remove_intf_link to continue makes the pad link
failure non-fatal, allowing the PCM to open normally. This
matches the intent of the surrounding loop which is designed
to handle multiple entities — a single failed pad link should
not prevent the others from being processed.

Note: this patch causes the remove_intf_link label to be unused,
producing a compiler warning. A follow-up cleanup patch could
remove the label and its associated code if the goto is no longer
reachable.

Signed-off-by: Stephen Brodie <author@example.com>
---
 sound/usb/media.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sound/usb/media.c b/sound/usb/media.c
index XXXXXXX..YYYYYYY 100644
--- a/sound/usb/media.c
+++ b/sound/usb/media.c
@@ -95,7 +95,7 @@ int snd_media_stream_init(struct snd_usb_substream *subs, struct snd_pcm *pcm,
 			ret = media_create_pad_link(entity, mixer_pad,
 						    &mctl->media_entity, 0,
 						    MEDIA_LNK_FL_ENABLED);
 			if (ret)
-				goto remove_intf_link;
+				continue;
